pdc_discovery.title: Upgrade webpack and friends for security patches

comments.body: @bess I noticed this PR hanging around.  I followed the instructions here: https://github.com/rails/webpacker/tree/5-x-stable and came up with https://github.com/pulibrary/pdc_discovery/tree/update-webpacker which seems to pass CI.  Did you want me to open a new PR?  It has a few additional updates, which may or may not be needed.

This ticket was prompted by a problem updating lib-jobs.princeton.edu in mid-June, after changing the playbook to run the `ruby_s` role instead of the `ruby` role. The playbook ran fine, but the first deploy after the playbook run failed. On investigation, it turned out there were multiple versions of ruby installed on the box. We suspect that the ruby version passenger was using was not the newly installed version. Gist of the run: https://gist.github.com/pulbot/ad1588075adb2d5bca178211089cdbfb

Notes from Ansible meeting 6/28:
- for implementing this, try decoupling the directory changes from the code/config changes, to reduce the number of moving parts
- turn off the workers while we update
- take one box at a time off the load-balancer to update
- see https://stackoverflow.com/a/66283091 for a potential approach to the directory renaming
Thanks @sandbergja @hackartisan @maxkadel @stephayers !
